{"TopicId":168732,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"Fourth monitor","CreatedByName":"JeeF","CreatedById":143053,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-12-20T18:43:20Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"JeeF","CreatedById":143053,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-12-20T18:43:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHey guys,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve been playing KSP in triple monitors (5760x1080) for a while now.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI do have a fourth monitor that I keep above the 3 panels, angled forward, where I can keep my hardware monitoring tools.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThen I thought today... that would be pretty cool if I could leave the 3 monitors for the scene and drag the mods and UI into the 4th screen, such as \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Engineer Redux (mod)\u0022\u003EKER\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there a way to do this? Perhaps a mod that I\u0027m not aware of?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSetup is something similar to this:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022maxresdefault.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ocXm3dPGWKc/maxresdefault.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-12-20T18:43:38Z\u0022 title=\u002212/20/2017 06:43  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 20, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by JeeF\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Li0n","CreatedById":142527,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-12-21T08:15:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNice setup. The only mod I know that could have help you is this one :\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed6589837207\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/157358-122-sideview-alpha-09-expand-your-horizon-or-crash-the-game/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;comment=2976537\u0026amp;embedComment=2976537\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment\u0022 style=\u0022height:297px;max-width:500px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s still on alpha, sarbian waited for the next version of KSP hoping it will be on Unity 5.6. But KSP 1.3.1 is still on Unity 5.4. KSP 1.4 should be on Unity 2017, when it comes out maybe sarbian will resurrect his mod.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sarbian","CreatedById":57146,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-12-21T17:46:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223249253\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022168732\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221513844139\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022142527\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Li0n\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 hours ago, Li0n said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwhen it comes out maybe sarbian will resurrect his mod.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s the plan\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Stone Blue","CreatedById":77721,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-12-21T18:03:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you have the hardware to handle it, you could give this one a look:\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed134184854\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/69089-stand-alone-map-view-multi-monitor-ksp-105plugin/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:209px;max-width:500px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, this one \u0022sorta\u0022 worked, right up to 1.2.2, and maybe 1.3.0... not sure if the plugin still works with 1.3.1, since that broke a lot of plugins....\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed4147207481\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/114181-abandoned-multi-monitor-screen-space/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:209px;max-width:500px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Wonderbreadninja","CreatedById":165043,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-12-21T18:13:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat I did was operate my game like a mission control using telemetry Data on my other monitors, (I might have a pic lying around...)\u00A0 I used the Telemachus mod, I had to re-compile it myself at one point because it was abandoned, but I believe. someone revived it and is continuing it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere Is my 6 monitor setup:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022XUUuR2m.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022614\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/XUUuR2m.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd the telemachus mod is:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/tcannonfodder/Telemachus/releases/tag/v1.5.33\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003ETelemachus on github\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-12-21T18:17:40Z\u0022 title=\u002212/21/2017 06:17  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 21, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Wonderbreadninja\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}